The first impression that this a tranquil corner of rural Worcestershire is misleading. Practically the whole square is devoted to intensive horticulture and agriculture controlled by large farms using modern mechanised equipment. Visitors are drawn to the area by the opportunities to "Pick Your Own" soft fruit.
The population is small, being limited to the farms, a few larger houses and part of a housing estate at Waresley
Despite the rural scene there is evidence in plenty of commerce and industry. A busy dual carriageway road carries heavy volumes of private and commercial traffic, ther is a new roadside restaurant, a caravan site and a garden shop.{
